;; The empty launch policy: a bootstrap that registers nothing. With it the
;; CLI's built-in fallback runs the program as a compile-time script on the
;; bare kernel + CTFE builtins — no stdlib, near-instant startup. Tools that
;; only need kernel primitives (tools/ast_json.caap, tools/canonicalize.caap)
;; run fastest this way:
;;
;;   caap tools/bare.caap tools/ast_json.caap FILE
null
